@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About DropShot - Real-Time Tennis Scoring &amp; Competition Software</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Medium" Class="mt-8 mb-8">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" Align="Align.Center" GutterBottom="true">About DropShot</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Align="Align.Center" Color="Color.Secondary" Class="mb-6" Style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto;">
        Real-time scoring and competition management for tennis players, clubs, and tournament organisers.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
        DropShot is a tennis scoring platform built for everyone who keeps the game running — from
        players tracking a casual match to clubs and organisers managing full tournaments. Score
        singles and doubles point-by-point with proper deuce, advantage, and tiebreak handling; drive
        courtside and broadcast scoreboards that update live across every connected screen; and run
        complete competitions from group stages through to a final, with fixtures, result
        verification, and player ratings all in one place.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
        We started DropShot because scoring a match and running a competition shouldn't mean
        paper draws, spreadsheets, and a scramble to work out who plays next. Everything updates in
        real time, so the score on court, the scoreboard on the wall, and the league table online
        are always the same.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-6 mb-2">Who DropShot is for</MudText>
    <ul class="mud-typography mud-typography-body1" style="padding-left:1.5rem;">
        <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Players</strong> — score casual singles or doubles matches with flexible rules,
            keep a saved history of every result, and track your form over time with an ELO rating
            that weights wins by margin of victory.
        </li>
        <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Clubs</strong> — manage club profiles, courts, and scheduling templates; appoint
            club administrators; and put live scoreboards on screens around the venue.
        </li>
        <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Organisers</strong> — run singles, doubles, mixed, or team competitions across
            round-robin groups and knockout brackets, with automatic progression as results are
            verified.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-6 mb-2">How it works</MudText>
    <ol class="mud-typography mud-typography-body1" style="padding-left:1.5rem;">
        <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Create a free account</strong> and add the players you regularly play with, or
            link to verified player profiles.
        </li>
        <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Set up a match or competition</strong> with a guided wizard — pick the format,
            the players, and the rules before play begins.
        </li>
        <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Score live</strong> from any device. Scores broadcast instantly to every
            scoreboard, phone, and browser connected to the match.
        </li>
        <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Results are saved automatically</strong> and feed into league tables, player
            ratings, and tournament progression.
        </li>
    </ol>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-6 mb-2">Built for real courts</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
        DropShot works on the web and as a native app for Android and iOS, so you can manage
        competitions from the clubhouse and score from courtside on your phone. QR-code login means
        you can sign in on a shared scoreboard screen in seconds, without typing a password in front
        of everyone.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
        Want to see everything DropShot can do? Browse the
        <MudLink Href="/features">full feature list</MudLink>, or
        <MudLink Href="/contact">get in touch</MudLink> — we read every message and would love your
        feedback.
    </MudText>

    <GoogleAd />

    <MudPaper Class="pa-6 mt-8 rounded-lg" Style="text-align: center; background: var(--mud-palette-primary); color: white;">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Style="color: inherit;" GutterBottom="true">
            Start scoring your next match
        </MudText>
        <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Dark" Size="Size.Large" Href="/Account/Register">
            Sign Up Free
        </MudButton>
    </MudPaper>
</MudContainer>
